// REFERENCE ONLY — this is the single-pane keybinding that install_keybinding.py merges
// (idempotently, preserving your other bindings) into your VS Code keybindings.json.
// Do NOT hand-merge this whole file; run `install/install.sh` or `install.sh --sync-keybinding`.
//
// What it does: binds cmd+ctrl+alt+9 to close BOTH side bars (idempotently). auto-continue.sh fires
// this chord (window-guarded) on a COLD worktree spawn BEFORE opening the Claude URI, so the spawned
// window is a single editor pane with no empty-Claude-sidebar "Message input" stealing focus from the
// pasted prompt — the root cause of ~40% cold auto-submit misses (fix 2026-06-06, dual-brain
// codex+Gemini + owner ruling). NO claude-vscode.focus, NO toggles — see keybindings-claude-focus.json
// for why those were rejected. Re-key ⇒ set HANDOFF_SIDEBAR_CLOSE_KEY and re-run --sync-keybinding.
[
  {
    "key": "cmd+ctrl+alt+9",
    "command": "runCommands",
    "args": { "commands": ["workbench.action.closeSidebar", "workbench.action.closeAuxiliaryBar"] }
  }
]
